<div id='panel'>
<h1>How to create an article</h1>
<h2>
[ <a href='edit.pl?id=how-to-create-an-article'>Edit</a> ]
</h2>

To create an article click on <a href='edit.pl?id=change-me'>this link</a> and follow the directions within the comments. Then use the panels below for directions on how to to create various article elements. 

<br /><br />
<span id='tab'>Creating a new paragraph</span>
<div id='panel'>
<h1>
To create a new paragraph in HTML you must surround the paragraph
with an opening <span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>p</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span> tag and a closing <span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/p</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span> tag.
</h1>

<br />
<div id='code'>
Paragraph One
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>p</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>Paragraph Two<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/p</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
</div>

<br />
<div id='panel' style='font-size:7pt;'>
Paragraph One 
<p>Paragraph Two</p>
</div>
</div>

<br />
<span id='tab'>Separating text on a new line</span>
<div id='panel'>
<h1>
To separate text on a new line in HTML you must add a <span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>br /</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span> tag before the text you want separated.
</h1>

<br />
<div id='code'>
A line of text.<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>br /</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>A new line of text.
</div>

<br />
<div id='panel' style='font-size:7pt;'>
A line of text.
<br />A new line of text.
</div>

<br />
<h1>
This method can also be used to separate text multiple new lines down.
</h1>

<br />
<div id='code'>
A line of text.<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>br /</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span><span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>br /</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>A new line of text.
</div>

<br />
<div id='panel' style='font-size:7pt;'>
A line of text.
<br /><br />A new line of text.
</div>
</div>

<br />
<span id='tab'>Adding multiple spaces to text</span>
<div id='panel'>
<h1>
To add multiple spaces between text in HTML you must type <span style='color:red;'>[&]nbsp;</span> between the text, instead of using regular space characters.
</h1>

<br />
<div id='code'>
Some text.<span style='color:red;'>[&]nbsp;</span><span style='color:red;'>[&]nbsp;</span>Some text two spaces away.
</div>

<br />
<div id='panel' style='font-size:7pt;'>
Some text.  Some text two spaces away.
</div>
</div>

<br />
<span id='tab'>Creating bold, underlined and italic text</span>
<div id='panel'>
<h1>
To create bold, underlined and italic text you must get familiar with the <span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>b</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span> <span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>u</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span> <span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>i</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span> HTML tags.
</h1>

<br />
<div id='code'>
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>b</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>Bold Text<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/b</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>u</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>Underlined Text<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/u</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>i</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>Italic Text<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/i</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
</div>

<br />
<div id='panel' style='font-size:7pt;'>
<b>Bold Text</b>
<br />
<u>Underlined Text</u>
<br />
<i>Italic Text</i>
</div>
</div>

<br />
<span id='tab'>Creating a caption</span>
<div id='panel'>
<h1>
A caption is an image that goes on the right hand side of the article with text beneath it. Caption images must have a width of 200 pixels to meet the standards of other articles. The code below shows how to make a caption.
<p>Captions must be placed before any article text and the article must have enough text for it to display properly.</p>
</h1>

<br />
<div id='code'>
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>div id='caption'</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>center</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>img src='</span><span style='color:green'>http://www.your-image-host.com/image.jpg</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>' /</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/center</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>br /</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />Your caption description goes here.
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/div</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
</div>

<br />
<div id='caption'>
<center>
<img src='../eccoserv/screenshots/ecco-splash-screenx200.gif'>
</center>
<br />
Your caption description goes here.
</div>
<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />
<br /><br /><br /><br />
</div>

<br />
<span id='tab'>Creating a panel</span>
<div id='panel'>
<h1>
A panel is a way to divide an article into sections.
A panel has a tab describing its contents an optional description heading, and the actual content.
</h1>

<br />
<div id='code'>
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>span id='tab'</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />Your tab description
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/span</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>div id='panel'</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>h1</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>Your optional description heading.<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/h1</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
<br />Your actual content area.
<br />
<span style='color:blue;'>[<]</span><span style='font-weight:bold;color:red;'>/div</span><span style='color:blue;'>[>]</span>
</div>

<br />
<span id='tab'>Your tab description</span>
<div id='panel'>
<h1>Your optional description heading.</h1>
Your actual content area.
</div>

</div>

</div>

